# logx enforcement

You are working inside **Aisphere Kernel**. Business code MUST use `github.com/aisphereio/kernel/logx` for all logging. logx applies to **every** Go file (logging is everywhere), unlike errorx which only applies to handler/service/repository/worker layers.

## Forbidden patterns (will fail CI)

In ALL Go files EXCEPT `*_test.go`, `logx/`, `examples/`, `cmd/`, `internal/`, `contrib/`:

```go
// ❌ FORBIDDEN — use logx instead
log.Printf("...")
log.Println("...")
fmt.Println("...")
fmt.Printf("...")
slog.Info("...")
slog.Default().Info("...")
slog.Debug(...)
slog.Warn(...)
slog.Error(...)
zap.L().Info("...")
zap.S().Info("...")
logrus.Info("...")

// ❌ FORBIDDEN — leaks credentials (logx redaction only works on logx fields)
logger.Info("login",
    logx.String("password", userPassword),
    logx.String("token", accessToken),
)
```

## Required patterns

```go
// ✅ Request-scoped logging (most common)
logx.FromContext(ctx).Info("skill created",
    logx.String("skill_id", id),
    logx.String("operation", "aihub.skill.create"),
)

// ✅ Service startup
logger, levelCtl, err := logx.New(cfg)
defer logger.Sync()
logger.Info("service started", logx.String("addr", ":8000"))

// ✅ Error log (auto-extracts errorx fields via duck typing, no cycle)
logger.Error("create failed",
    logx.String("operation", "aihub.skill.create"),
    logx.Err(err),
)

// ✅ Inject request-scoped fields at handler boundary
ctx = logx.Inject(ctx, logger,
    logx.String("request_id", reqID),
    logx.String("trace_id", traceID),
    logx.String("subject_id", userID),
)
// All downstream logx.FromContext(ctx) calls auto-include these fields.
```

## API cheatsheet

### Bootstrap

| Function | Use for |
|---|---|
| `logx.New(cfg)` | Bootstrap logger (returns Logger + LevelController) |
| `logx.DefaultConfig(env)` | Sane defaults for dev/staging/prod |
| `logx.Noop()` | Discard all logs (tests, disabled features) |
| `logx.FromContext(ctx)` | Request-scoped logger (Noop if none) |
| `logx.Inject(ctx, logger, fields...)` | Attach logger + fields to ctx |
| `logx.Sync(logger)` | Flush buffers before exit |

### Logger methods

```go
logger.Debug(msg, fields...)
logger.Info(msg, fields...)
logger.Warn(msg, fields...)
logger.Error(msg, fields...)
logger.With(fields...) Logger        // persistent fields
logger.Named(name) Logger            // module tag
logger.WithContext(ctx) Logger
logger.Enabled(level) bool
logger.Sync() error
```

### Field constructors

```go
logx.String(k, v)        logx.Int(k, v)        logx.Int64(k, v)
logx.Uint64(k, v)        logx.Bool(k, v)       logx.Float64(k, v)
logx.Duration(k, v)      logx.Time(k, v)       logx.Any(k, v)
logx.Event(name)         logx.Err(err)         logx.Group(k, fields...)
```

`logx.Err(err)` auto-extracts error_code / http_status / retryable / grpc_code from any error implementing those methods (works with errorx without importing it — no cycle).

### Pre-built log helpers

| Function | Use for |
|---|---|
| `logx.LogAccess(logger, AccessEvent{...})` | HTTP access log |
| `logx.LogExternalCall(logger, ExternalCall{...})` | Upstream API call log |
| `logx.LogError(logger, msg, ErrorLog{...})` | Standardized error log |
| `logx.LogAuditHint(logger, AuditHint{...})` | Audit breadcrumb |

### HTTP / RPC middleware

```go
logx.HTTPAccessLog(logger, cfg)         → http middleware
logx.Recovery(logger, opts...)          → http panic recovery middleware
logx.ServerLogging(logger, extract)     → RPC server logging
logx.ClientLogging(logger, extract)     → RPC client logging
logx.RPCRecovery(logger, handler)       → RPC panic recovery
logx.LevelHTTPHandler(controller)       → runtime level control HTTP endpoint
```

## Redaction (auto)

logx automatically redacts these field keys:

```text
password / passwd / pwd / token / access_token / refresh_token / id_token
secret / client_secret / authorization / cookie / set_cookie
api_key / private_key / ak / sk
```

Customize via `Config.Redact`. **Never log credentials directly** — redaction is a safety net, not a license to log secrets.

## Sampling (high-QPS logs)

```go
cfg.Sampling = logx.SamplingConfig{
    Enabled:  true,
    Every:    100,
    First:    10,
    Window:   time.Second,
    MinLevel: logx.DebugLevel.String(),  // only sample debug/info; warn+ always kept
}
```

**Warn and error are NEVER sampled.**

